8 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Orientation course -- annual training. (1) Under the supervision of the
9 supreme court, a course of study must be presented as soon as is practical following each general election.
10 Actual and necessary travel expenses, as defined and provided in 2-18-501 through 2-18-503, and the costs of
11 registration and books and other materials must be paid to the elected or appointed judge or standing master
12 for attending the course by the county in which the judge or standing master holds or will hold court and must
13 be charged against that county office of the court administrator provided for in 3-1-701.
14 (2) There must be two mandatory annual training sessions supervised by the supreme court for all
15 elected and appointed judges or standing masters. One of the training sessions may be held in conjunction with
16 the Montana magistrates' association convention. Actual and necessary travel expenses, as defined and
17 provided in 2-18-501 through 2-18-503, and the costs of registration and books and other materials must be
18 paid to the elected or appointed judges or standing masters for attending the sessions by the county in which
19 the judge or standing master holds or will hold court and must be charged against that county office of the court
20 administrator provided for in 3-1-701.
21 (3) Each judge or standing master shall attend the training sessions provided for in subsection (2).
22 Failure to attend disqualifies the judge or standing master from office and creates a vacancy in the office.
23 However, the supreme court may excuse a judge or standing master from attendance because of illness, a
24 death in the family, or any other good cause.
25 (4) A judge or standing master presiding over child custody proceedings shall complete:
26 (a) not less than 20 hours of initial orientation training; and
27 (b) not less than 15 hours of ongoing training every 2 years.
